Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk.     "categories" : [ "IDR 27,000 Asian, Indonesian Dinner, Brunch Delivery, Takeout, Reservations, Outdoor Seating, Seating, Waitstaff, Parking Available, Street Parking Address: Jln. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk.     "categories" : [ "IDR 27,000 Asian, Indonesian Dinner, Brunch Delivery, Takeout, Reservations, Outdoor Seating, Seating, Waitstaff, Parking Available, Street Parking Address: Jln. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk.     "categories" : [ "IDR 27,000 Asian, Indonesian Dinner, Brunch Delivery, Takeout, Reservations, Outdoor Seating, Seating, Waitstaff, Parking Available, Street Parking Address: Jln. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Soekarno Hatta no. 111, Pekanbaru 28292, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Riau Province  >  Pekanbaru Phone Number: +62 761 27678 PT Sushi Tei Indonesia opened its first outlet in Jakarta in 2003, bringing the renowned Japanese restaurant brand to sushi enthusiasts in Indonesia. It has since then subsequently grown well, opening up new outlets in other major cities in Indonesia: Bandung, Surabaya, Medan and Bali, as well as well as expanding its presence in Jakarta. Currently there are nineteen Sushi Tei outlets in total, with ten of them spread across Greater Jakarta. Sushi Tei's outlets are best known for their simple-yet-modern approach to its open kitchen concept, employing distinctive touches of Japanese culture. Sushi Tei's open kitchen allows its patrons to take a look at what's going on as their orders are being prepared. Sushi Tei is also proud to have become the first sushi restaurant in Indonesia to feature the characteristic sushi bar with a conveyor belt. Sushi Tei aims to provide an exceptional dining experience that exceeds the expectations of customers, by blending the authenticity of Japanese highly-praised taste and a signature touch of local flavor, with the highest level of service and comfort. Paying attention not only to taste, Sushi Tei focuses also on the quality of its food as well as service. To enhance the customers' confidence in dining, Sushi Tei has implemented the world-renowned HACCP (Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Point) standard in its food safety management system. The standard guarantees the quality and safety of all food, especially the sashimi menu, served at all Sushi Tei outlets. Knowing that the HACCP is always in action, Sushi Tei customers can now enjoy their wonderful meals safely and wholesomely. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Soekarno Hatta no. 111, Pekanbaru 28292, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Riau Province  >  Pekanbaru Phone Number: +62 761 27678 PT Sushi Tei Indonesia opened its first outlet in Jakarta in 2003, bringing the renowned Japanese restaurant brand to sushi enthusiasts in Indonesia. It has since then subsequently grown well, opening up new outlets in other major cities in Indonesia: Bandung, Surabaya, Medan and Bali, as well as well as expanding its presence in Jakarta. Currently there are nineteen Sushi Tei outlets in total, with ten of them spread across Greater Jakarta. Sushi Tei's outlets are best known for their simple-yet-modern approach to its open kitchen concept, employing distinctive touches of Japanese culture. Sushi Tei's open kitchen allows its patrons to take a look at what's going on as their orders are being prepared. Sushi Tei is also proud to have become the first sushi restaurant in Indonesia to feature the characteristic sushi bar with a conveyor belt. Sushi Tei aims to provide an exceptional dining experience that exceeds the expectations of customers, by blending the authenticity of Japanese highly-praised taste and a signature touch of local flavor, with the highest level of service and comfort. Paying attention not only to taste, Sushi Tei focuses also on the quality of its food as well as service. To enhance the customers' confidence in dining, Sushi Tei has implemented the world-renowned HACCP (Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Point) standard in its food safety management system. The standard guarantees the quality and safety of all food, especially the sashimi menu, served at all Sushi Tei outlets. Knowing that the HACCP is always in action, Sushi Tei customers can now enjoy their wonderful meals safely and wholesomely. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. It has since then subsequently grown well, opening up new outlets in other major cities in Indonesia: Bandung, Surabaya, Medan and Bali, as well as well as expanding its presence in Jakarta. Currently there are nineteen Sushi Tei outlets in total, with ten of them spread across Greater Jakarta. Sushi Tei's outlets are best known for their simple-yet-modern approach to its open kitchen concept, employing distinctive touches of Japanese culture. Sushi Tei's open kitchen allows its patrons to take a look at what's going on as their orders are being prepared. Sushi Tei is also proud to have become the first sushi restaurant in Indonesia to feature the characteristic sushi bar with a conveyor belt. Sushi Tei aims to provide an exceptional dining experience that exceeds the expectations of customers, by blending the authenticity of Japanese highly-praised taste and a signature touch of local flavor, with the highest level of service and comfort. Paying attention not only to taste, Sushi Tei focuses also on the quality of its food as well as service. To enhance the customers' confidence in dining, Sushi Tei has implemented the world-renowned HACCP (Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Point) standard in its food safety management system. The standard guarantees the quality and safety of all food, especially the sashimi menu, served at all Sushi Tei outlets. Knowing that the HACCP is always in action, Sushi Tei customers can now enjoy their wonderful meals safely and wholesomely. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Soekarno Hatta no. 111, Pekanbaru 28292, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Riau Province  >  Pekanbaru Phone Number: +62 761 27678 PT Sushi Tei Indonesia opened its first outlet in Jakarta in 2003, bringing the renowned Japanese restaurant brand to sushi enthusiasts in Indonesia. It has since then subsequently grown well, opening up new outlets in other major cities in Indonesia: Bandung, Surabaya, Medan and Bali, as well as well as expanding its presence in Jakarta. Currently there are nineteen Sushi Tei outlets in total, with ten of them spread across Greater Jakarta. Sushi Tei's outlets are best known for their simple-yet-modern approach to its open kitchen concept, employing distinctive touches of Japanese culture. Sushi Tei's open kitchen allows its patrons to take a look at what's going on as their orders are being prepared. Sushi Tei is also proud to have become the first sushi restaurant in Indonesia to feature the characteristic sushi bar with a conveyor belt. Sushi Tei aims to provide an exceptional dining experience that exceeds the expectations of customers, by blending the authenticity of Japanese highly-praised taste and a signature touch of local flavor, with the highest level of service and comfort. Paying attention not only to taste, Sushi Tei focuses also on the quality of its food as well as service. To enhance the customers' confidence in dining, Sushi Tei has implemented the world-renowned HACCP (Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Point) standard in its food safety management system. The standard guarantees the quality and safety of all food, especially the sashimi menu, served at all Sushi Tei outlets. Knowing that the HACCP is always in action, Sushi Tei customers can now enjoy their wonderful meals safely and wholesomely. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. Soekarno Hatta no. 111, Pekanbaru 28292, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Riau Province  >  Pekanbaru Phone Number: +62 761 27678 PT Sushi Tei Indonesia opened its first outlet in Jakarta in 2003, bringing the renowned Japanese restaurant brand to sushi enthusiasts in Indonesia. It has since then subsequently grown well, opening up new outlets in other major cities in Indonesia: Bandung, Surabaya, Medan and Bali, as well as well as expanding its presence in Jakarta. Currently there are nineteen Sushi Tei outlets in total, with ten of them spread across Greater Jakarta. Sushi Tei's outlets are best known for their simple-yet-modern approach to its open kitchen concept, employing distinctive touches of Japanese culture. Sushi Tei's open kitchen allows its patrons to take a look at what's going on as their orders are being prepared. Sushi Tei is also proud to have become the first sushi restaurant in Indonesia to feature the characteristic sushi bar with a conveyor belt. Sushi Tei aims to provide an exceptional dining experience that exceeds the expectations of customers, by blending the authenticity of Japanese highly-praised taste and a signature touch of local flavor, with the highest level of service and comfort. Paying attention not only to taste, Sushi Tei focuses also on the quality of its food as well as service. To enhance the customers' confidence in dining, Sushi Tei has implemented the world-renowned HACCP (Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Point) standard in its food safety management system. The standard guarantees the quality and safety of all food, especially the sashimi menu, served at all Sushi Tei outlets. Knowing that the HACCP is always in action, Sushi Tei customers can now enjoy their wonderful meals safely and wholesomely. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Hal tersebut menjelaskan persiapan hidangan itu sendiri yang membutuhkan bahan lebih dari memasak nasi biasa dan juga jenis tambahan lauk. It has since then subsequently grown well, opening up new outlets in other major cities in Indonesia: Bandung, Surabaya, Medan and Bali, as well as well as expanding its presence in Jakarta. Currently there are nineteen Sushi Tei outlets in total, with ten of them spread across Greater Jakarta. Sushi Tei's outlets are best known for their simple-yet-modern approach to its open kitchen concept, employing distinctive touches of Japanese culture. Sushi Tei's open kitchen allows its patrons to take a look at what's going on as their orders are being prepared. Sushi Tei is also proud to have become the first sushi restaurant in Indonesia to feature the characteristic sushi bar with a conveyor belt. Sushi Tei aims to provide an exceptional dining experience that exceeds the expectations of customers, by blending the authenticity of Japanese highly-praised taste and a signature touch of local flavor, with the highest level of service and comfort. Paying attention not only to taste, Sushi Tei focuses also on the quality of its food as well as service. To enhance the customers' confidence in dining, Sushi Tei has implemented the world-renowned HACCP (Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Point) standard in its food safety management system. The standard guarantees the quality and safety of all food, especially the sashimi menu, served at all Sushi Tei outlets. Knowing that the HACCP is always in action, Sushi Tei customers can now enjoy their wonderful meals safely and wholesomely.     } ],
    "time" : [ {
      "open" : 11,

    } ],
    "categories" : [ "IDR 27,000 Asian, Indonesian Dinner, Brunch Delivery, Takeout, Reservations, Outdoor Seating, Seating, Waitstaff, Parking Available, Street Parking Address: Jln. Tgk Nyak Arief | In Front of Asrama Haji, Banda Aceh 23114, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Aceh  >  Banda Aceh Phone Number: +62 851-0543-7707 Nasi Uduk Klapa Gading (R) Depan Asrama Haji Lingke - Banda Aceh - Indonesia. Nasi uduk literally means \"mixed rice\" in Betawi dialect, related with Indonesian term aduk (\"mix\"). The name describes the dish preparation itself which requires more ingredients than common steamed rice cooking and also varieties of additional side dishes. Nasi uduk secara harfiah berarti \"nasi campur\" dalam dialek Betawi, terkait dengan \"Aduk\" istilah Indonesia (\"campuran\"). Soekarno Hatta no. 111, Pekanbaru 28292, Indonesia Location: Asia  >  Indonesia  >  Sumatra  >  Riau Province  >  Pekanbaru Phone Number: +62 761 27678 PT Sushi Tei Indonesia opened its first outlet in Jakarta in 2003, bringing the renowned Japanese restaurant brand to sushi enthusiasts in Indonesia. It has since then subsequently grown well, opening up new outlets in other major cities in Indonesia: Bandung, Surabaya, Medan and Bali, as well as well as expanding its presence in Jakarta. Currently there are nineteen Sushi Tei outlets in total, with ten of them spread across Greater Jakarta. Sushi Tei's outlets are best known for their simple-yet-modern approach to its open kitchen concept, employing distinctive touches of Japanese culture. Sushi Tei's open kitchen allows its patrons to take a look at what's going on as their orders are being prepared. Sushi Tei is also proud to have become the first sushi restaurant in Indonesia to feature the characteristic sushi bar with a conveyor belt. Sushi Tei aims to provide an exceptional dining experience that exceeds the expectations of customers, by blending the authenticity of Japanese highly-praised taste and a signature touch of local flavor, with the highest level of service and comfort. Paying attention not only to taste, Sushi Tei focuses also on the quality of its food as well as service. To enhance the customers' confidence in dining, Sushi Tei has implemented the world-renowned HACCP (Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Point) standard in its food safety management system. The standard guarantees the quality and safety of all food, especially the sashimi menu, served at all Sushi Tei outlets. Knowing that the HACCP is always in action, Sushi Tei customers can now enjoy their wonderful meals safely and wholesomely.
